<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Statistics — Mean, Median, Mode, Variance &amp; Distributions</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fredoka+One&family=Nunito:wght@400;600;700;800&family=Fira+Code:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root{
  --mean-blue:#3b82f6;--mean-sky:#0ea5e9;
  --med-orange:#f97316;--med-amber:#f59e0b;
  --var-green:#10b981;--var-teal:#14b8a6;
  --dist-purple:#8b5cf6;--dist-pink:#ec4899;
  --bg:#0f1117;--bg2:#161b27;--text:#e8eaf0;--muted:#8892a4;
  --card:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);--radius:16px;
}
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box;}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth;}
body{font-family:'Nunito',sans-serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);overflow-x:hidden;}

/* ── HERO ── */
.hero{min-height:100vh;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;text-align:center;padding:40px 20px;
  background:radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 50% 0%,rgba(59,130,246,0.18) 0%,transparent 70%),
             radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 40% at 80% 90%,rgba(139,92,246,0.12) 0%,transparent 60%),var(--bg);
  position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
.hero-badge{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--mean-blue);background:rgba(59,130,246,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.3);padding:6px 16px;border-radius:50px;letter-spacing:2px;margin-bottom:24px;display:inline-block;}
.hero h1{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:clamp(2.4rem,7vw,5rem);line-height:1.05;
  background:linear-gradient(135deg,#fff 15%,var(--mean-blue) 30%,var(--med-orange) 50%,var(--var-green) 70%,var(--dist-purple) 85%);
  -webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;background-clip:text;margin-bottom:16px;}
.hero p{font-size:20px;color:var(--muted);max-width:720px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:36px;}
.topic-pills{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px;justify-content:center;max-width:900px;}
.pill{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:13px;padding:8px 18px;border-radius:50px;font-weight:500;border:1px solid;}
.pill-mean{color:var(--mean-blue);border-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5);background:rgba(59,130,246,0.1);}
.pill-med{color:var(--med-orange);border-color:rgba(249,115,22,0.5);background:rgba(249,115,22,0.1);}
.pill-var{color:var(--var-green);border-color:rgba(16,185,129,0.5);background:rgba(16,185,129,0.1);}
.pill-dist{color:var(--dist-purple);border-color:rgba(139,92,246,0.5);background:rgba(139,92,246,0.1);}
.float-code{position:absolute;font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);pointer-events:none;user-select:none;white-space:nowrap;}

/* ── LAYOUT ── */
.wrapper{max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 20px 100px;}

/* ── SECTION DIVIDER ── */
.section-divider{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin:70px 0 28px;}
.section-divider .label{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:26px;white-space:nowrap;}
.section-divider::after{content:'';flex:1;height:1px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,var(--accent,rgba(255,255,255,0.1)),transparent);}
.div-mean .label{color:var(--mean-blue);}.div-mean{--accent:rgba(59,130,246,0.4);}
.div-med .label{color:var(--med-orange);}.div-med{--accent:rgba(249,115,22,0.4);}
.div-var .label{color:var(--var-green);}.div-var{--accent:rgba(16,185,129,0.4);}
.div-dist .label{color:var(--dist-purple);}.div-dist{--accent:rgba(139,92,246,0.4);}
.div-quiz .label{color:#f472b6;}.div-quiz{--accent:rgba(244,114,182,0.4);}

/* ── CARDS ── */
.card{background:var(--card);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:28px 32px;margin-bottom:20px;position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
.card::before{content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,var(--stripe,rgba(255,255,255,0.15)),transparent);}
.card-mean::before{--stripe:rgba(59,130,246,0.6);}
.card-med::before{--stripe:rgba(249,115,22,0.6);}
.card-var::before{--stripe:rgba(16,185,129,0.6);}
.card-dist::before{--stripe:rgba(139,92,246,0.6);}
.card h3{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:20px;margin-bottom:12px;}
.card-mean h3{color:var(--mean-blue);}
.card-med h3{color:var(--med-orange);}
.card-var h3{color:var(--var-green);}
.card-dist h3{color:var(--dist-purple);}
.card p,.card li{font-size:17px;line-height:1.75;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.72);}
.card ul,.card ol{margin-left:22px;margin-top:8px;}.card li{margin-bottom:5px;}.card strong{color:#fff;}
.tip-box{background:rgba(59,130,246,0.06);border-left:3px solid var(--mean-blue);border-radius:8px;padding:13px 16px;margin-top:16px;font-size:16px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);}
.tip-box-med{background:rgba(249,115,22,0.06);border-left-color:var(--med-orange);}
.tip-box-var{background:rgba(16,185,129,0.06);border-left-color:var(--var-green);}
.tip-box-dist{background:rgba(139,92,246,0.06);border-left-color:var(--dist-purple);}
.code-line{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;background:#0a0f1a;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);padding:14px 18px;border-radius:10px;font-size:15px;color:#7ee787;margin:12px 0;white-space:pre-wrap;line-height:1.6;}
.output-console{background:#000;border:2px solid rgba(126,231,135,0.3);border-radius:10px;padding:16px;font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;color:#7ee787;font-size:14px;min-height:60px;margin-top:12px;line-height:1.8;overflow-x:auto;}

/* ── INTERACTIVE ── */
.demo-box{background:#0a0f1a;border-radius:12px;padding:24px;margin:20px 0;border:2px solid;}
.box-mean{border-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.3);}
.box-med{border-color:rgba(249,115,22,0.3);}
.box-var{border-color:rgba(16,185,129,0.3);}
.box-dist{border-color:rgba(139,92,246,0.3);}
.box-title{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:18px;text-align:center;margin-bottom:20px;}
.box-mean .box-title{color:var(--mean-blue);}
.box-med .box-title{color:var(--med-orange);}
.box-var .box-title{color:var(--var-green);}
.box-dist .box-title{color:var(--dist-purple);}
input[type="text"],input[type="number"],select{width:100%;padding:12px 16px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.15);border-radius:8px;color:var(--text);font-family:'Nunito',sans-serif;font-size:15px;margin:8px 0;}
input:focus,select:focus{outline:none;border-color:var(--mean-blue);}
.btn{padding:12px 32px;border:none;border-radius:50px;font-family:'Nunito',sans-serif;font-size:16px;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.3s;margin:8px 4px;}
.btn-mean{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--mean-blue),var(--mean-sky));color:white;}
.btn-med{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--med-orange),var(--med-amber));color:#000;}
.btn-var{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--var-green),var(--var-teal));color:#000;}
.btn-dist{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--dist-purple),var(--dist-pink));color:white;}
.btn:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);box-shadow:0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);}
.result-box{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);border-radius:10px;padding:20px;margin-top:16px;}

/* ── FORMULA BOX ── */
.formula-box{background:rgba(0,0,0,0.35);border:2px solid;border-radius:14px;padding:24px;text-align:center;margin:20px 0;}
.formula-box .formula{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:clamp(18px,4vw,26px);letter-spacing:1px;margin:12px 0;}
.formula-box .explain{font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:2;}

/* ── BAR VIS ── */
.bar-row{display:flex;align-items:end;gap:6px;height:140px;padding:0 10px;margin:20px 0;}
.bar-col{display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;flex:1;gap:4px;}
.bar{border-radius:6px 6px 0 0;width:100%;min-width:20px;transition:height 0.4s ease;}
.bar-label{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);}
.bar-val{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;}

/* ── CONCEPT GRID ── */
.concept-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:16px;margin:20px 0;}
.concept-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);border:2px solid;border-radius:12px;padding:20px;text-align:center;transition:all 0.3s;}
.concept-card:hover{transform:translateY(-3px);box-shadow:0 8px 25px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);}

/* ── STEP TRACE ── */
.step-trace{display:grid;gap:8px;margin:16px 0;}
.step{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 18px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;border-left:3px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);}
.step-num{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:22px;min-width:32px;}
.step.active{border-left-color:var(--var-green);background:rgba(16,185,129,0.08);}

/* ── DISTRIBUTION CANVAS ── */
.dist-canvas{width:100%;height:200px;border-radius:10px;margin:16px 0;background:#0a0f1a;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);}

/* ── QUIZ ── */
.quiz-wrap{background:var(--card);border:1px solid rgba(244,114,182,0.2);border-radius:20px;padding:36px 32px;margin-top:10px;}
.quiz-header{text-align:center;margin-bottom:32px;}
.quiz-header h2{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:2rem;color:#f472b6;margin-bottom:8px;}
.quiz-header p{font-size:17px;color:var(--muted);}
.quiz-scorebar{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:20px;margin-bottom:28px;flex-wrap:wrap;}
.score-chip{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:13px;padding:8px 20px;border-radius:50px;background:rgba(244,114,182,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(244,114,182,0.3);color:#f472b6;letter-spacing:1px;}
.progress-bar-wrap{flex:1;max-width:260px;height:6px;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden;}
.progress-bar-fill{height:100%;background:linear-gradient(90deg,#f472b6,#c084fc);border-radius:3px;transition:width 0.4s ease;width:0%;}
.qcard{background:#0a0f1a;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-radius:14px;padding:24px 26px;margin-bottom:18px;transition:border-color 0.3s;}
.qcard.ok{border-color:rgba(57,255,20,0.35);}.qcard.bad{border-color:rgba(248,81,73,0.35);}
.qnum{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:10px;color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:2px;margin-bottom:9px;}
.qtext{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:19px;color:#fff;margin-bottom:18px;line-height:1.4;}
.opts{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:9px;}
@media(max-width:480px){.opts{grid-template-columns:1fr;}}
.opt{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);border-radius:10px;padding:12px 15px;font-family:'Nunito',sans-serif;font-size:15px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);cursor:pointer;text-align:left;transition:all 0.18s;line-height:1.4;}
.opt:hover:not(:disabled){background:rgba(244,114,182,0.08);border-color:rgba(244,114,182,0.4);color:#fff;transform:translateX(2px);}
.opt.correct{background:rgba(57,185,80,0.12);border-color:#3fb950;color:#3fb950;font-weight:700;}
.opt.wrong{background:rgba(248,81,73,0.1);border-color:#f85149;color:#f85149;opacity:0.75;}
.opt:disabled{cursor:default;}
.feedback{margin-top:12px;font-size:15px;min-height:20px;padding:0 2px;font-weight:600;}
.feedback.ok{color:#3fb950;}.feedback.bad{color:#f85149;}
.final-box{display:none;text-align:center;padding:40px 20px;}
.final-box.show{display:block;}
.final-score{font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:clamp(3rem,10vw,5.5rem);margin-bottom:8px;}
.final-score.perfect{color:var(--var-green);filter:drop-shadow(0 0 20px rgba(16,185,129,0.5));}
.final-score.great{color:var(--dist-purple);filter:drop-shadow(0 0 20px rgba(139,92,246,0.5));}
.final-score.okish{color:var(--mean-blue);}
.final-stars{font-size:32px;letter-spacing:8px;margin:12px 0;}
.final-msg{font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:1px;line-height:2.2;white-space:pre-line;margin-bottom:24px;}
@media(max-width:600px){.card{padding:20px 18px;}.quiz-wrap{padding:24px 16px;}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ╔══════════ HERO ══════════╗ -->
<div class="hero">
  <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;overflow:hidden;pointer-events:none;">
    <div class="float-code" style="top:12%;left:4%;">mean = sum(data)/len(data)<br>median = sorted middle<br>mode = most frequent</div>
    <div class="float-code" style="top:65%;left:2%;">variance = Σ(x-μ)²/n<br>std_dev = √variance<br>spread of data</div>
    <div class="float-code" style="top:20%;right:3%;">normal distribution<br>bell curve shape<br>68-95-99.7 rule</div>
    <div class="float-code" style="top:70%;right:4%;">df.describe()<br>df.mean()<br>df.std()</div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-badge">// DATA SCIENCE · STATISTICS FUNDAMENTALS //</div>
  <h1>Statistics:<br>Understanding<br>Your Data</h1>
  <p>Before you can visualize data, you need to understand it! Learn mean, median, mode, variance, standard deviation, and data distributions — the foundation of every chart and graph you'll ever make.</p>
  <div class="topic-pills">
    <div class="pill pill-mean">📊 Mean (Average)</div>
    <div class="pill pill-med">📍 Median &amp; Mode</div>
    <div class="pill pill-var">📏 Variance &amp; Std Dev</div>
    <div class="pill pill-dist">🔔 Distributions</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper">

<!-- ╔══════════ MEAN ══════════╗ -->
<div class="section-divider div-mean">
  <div class="label">📊 Mean (Average)</div>
</div>

<div class="card card-mean">
  <h3>What is the Mean?</h3>
  <p>The <strong>mean</strong> is what most people call the "average." It tells you the <strong>typical value</strong> in a dataset by spreading all the values equally.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:12px;">Imagine 5 friends have ₹10, ₹20, ₹30, ₹40, and ₹50. If they pooled ALL their money and split it equally, each person would get <strong>₹30</strong>. That's the mean!</p>

  <div class="formula-box" style="border-color:var(--mean-blue);">
    <div style="font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:16px;color:var(--mean-blue);">Formula</div>
    <div class="formula" style="color:var(--mean-blue);">Mean = Sum of all values ÷ Number of values</div>
    <div class="explain">
      Mean = (10 + 20 + 30 + 40 + 50) ÷ 5 = 150 ÷ 5 = <strong style="color:#fff;">30</strong>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card card-mean">
  <h3>Calculating Mean Step by Step</h3>
  <p>Let's calculate the mean test score for 7 students:</p>

  <div style="background:rgba(59,130,246,0.08);border:2px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.25);border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin:16px 0;">
    <strong style="color:var(--mean-blue);">Scores: 85, 92, 78, 95, 88, 73, 91</strong>
    <div class="step-trace" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <div class="step active"><div class="step-num" style="color:var(--mean-blue);">1</div><div><strong>Add all values:</strong> 85 + 92 + 78 + 95 + 88 + 73 + 91 = <strong style="color:var(--mean-blue);">602</strong></div></div>
      <div class="step active"><div class="step-num" style="color:var(--mean-blue);">2</div><div><strong>Count the values:</strong> There are <strong style="color:var(--mean-blue);">7</strong> scores</div></div>
      <div class="step active"><div class="step-num" style="color:var(--mean-blue);">3</div><div><strong>Divide:</strong> 602 ÷ 7 = <strong style="color:var(--mean-blue);">86.0</strong></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="code-line">scores = [85, 92, 78, 95, 88, 73, 91]

# Method 1: Manual calculation
mean = sum(scores) / len(scores)
print("Mean:", mean)

# Method 2: Using statistics module
import statistics
mean = statistics.mean(scores)
print("Mean:", mean)

# Method 3: Using pandas
import pandas as pd
df = pd.DataFrame({"Score": scores})
print("Mean:", df["Score"].mean())</div>

  <div class="output-console">Mean: 86.0
Mean: 86.0
Mean: 86.0</div>
</div>

<div class="card card-mean">
  <h3>The Mean Has a Weakness!</h3>
  <p>The mean can be <strong>pulled by extreme values</strong> (outliers). One really big or small number can make the mean misleading!</p>

  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px;margin:20px 0;">
    <div style="background:rgba(16,185,129,0.08);border:2px solid rgba(16,185,129,0.25);border-radius:12px;padding:20px;text-align:center;">
      <strong style="color:var(--var-green);font-size:16px;">Without Outlier</strong>
      <div style="font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:10px;">Salaries: ₹30K, ₹35K, ₹40K, ₹45K, ₹50K</div>
      <div style="font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:28px;color:var(--var-green);margin-top:8px;">Mean: ₹40K</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);">Feels accurate! ✅</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:rgba(248,81,73,0.08);border:2px solid rgba(248,81,73,0.25);border-radius:12px;padding:20px;text-align:center;">
      <strong style="color:#f85149;font-size:16px;">With Outlier</strong>
      <div style="font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:10px;">Salaries: ₹30K, ₹35K, ₹40K, ₹45K, <span style="color:#f85149;">₹500K</span></div>
      <div style="font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:28px;color:#f85149;margin-top:8px;">Mean: ₹130K</div>
      <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);">Misleading! Most earn way less ❌</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="tip-box">⚠️ <strong>When Mean Lies:</strong> If your data has outliers (extreme values), the mean gets "pulled" toward them. In those cases, the <strong>median</strong> is a better measure!</div>
</div>

<!-- Interactive: Mean Calculator -->
<div class="demo-box box-mean">
  <div class="box-title">🧮 Interactive: Mean Calculator</div>
  <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:20px;">Enter numbers separated by commas and see the mean calculated step by step!</p>
  <label style="color:var(--text);font-weight:600;display:block;margin-bottom:4px;">Your Data:</label>
  <input type="text" id="meanInput" placeholder="e.g., 85, 92, 78, 95, 88" value="85, 92, 78, 95, 88, 73, 91">
  <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:12px;">
    <button class="btn btn-mean" onclick="calcMean()">Calculate Mean 📊</button>
  </div>
  <div id="meanOutput"></div>
</div>


<!-- ╔══════════ MEDIAN & MODE ══════════╗ -->
<div class="section-divider div-med">
  <div class="label">📍 Median &amp; Mode</div>
</div>

<div class="card card-med">
  <h3>What is the Median?</h3>
  <p>The <strong>median</strong> is the <strong>middle value</strong> when you arrange all numbers in order. Half the values are below it, half are above. It's like the person standing in the exact center of a line!</p>

  <div class="formula-box" style="border-color:var(--med-orange);">
    <div style="font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:16px;color:var(--med-orange);">How to Find the Median</div>
    <div class="formula" style="color:var(--med-orange);font-size:18px;">1. Sort the numbers &nbsp; 2. Find the middle one</div>
  </div>

  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px;margin:20px 0;">
    <div style="background:rgba(249,115,22,0.08);border:2px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.25);border-radius:12px;padding:20px;">
      <strong style="color:var(--med-orange);font-size:15px;">Odd Count (easy!)</strong>
      <div style="font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:10px;">
        Data: 7, 2, 9, 4, 5<br>
        Sorted: 2, 4, <strong style="color:var(--med-orange);font-size:18px;">5</strong>, 7, 9<br>
        <span style="color:var(--med-orange);">↑ Middle value!</span>
      </div>
      <div style="font-family:'Fredoka One',cursive;font-size:22px;color:var(--med-orange);margin-top:8px;text-align:center;">Median = 5</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:rgba(249,115,22,0.08);border:2px solid rgba(249,115,22,0.25);border-radius:12px;padding:20px;">
      <strong style="color:var(--med-orange);font-size:15px;">Even Count (average the 2 middles)</strong>
      <div style="font-family:'Fira Code',monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:10px;">
        Data: 3, 8, 1, 6<br>
        Sorted: 1, <strong style="color:var(--med-orange);">3</strong>, <strong style="color:var(--med-orange);">6</strong>, 8<br>
